### Have you read the Contributing Guidelines on issues?

- [X] I have read the [Contributing Guidelines on issues](https://github.com/webdriverio/webdriverio/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#reporting-new-issues).

### WebdriverIO Version

latest

### Node.js Version

18.18.1

### Mode

WDIO Testrunner

### Which capabilities are you using?

```typescript
services: [
	['browserstack', {
		app: 'bs_custom_id',
		browserstackLocal: true,
		testObservability: false,
		opts: {
			localIdentifier: 'some_local_identifier',
		}
	}]
],
capabilities: [{
	projectName: 'some_project_name',
	buildName: 'some_build_name',
	debug: true,
	networkLogs: true,
	device: 'iPhone 14',
	os_version: '16',
}]
```


### What happened?

When I run my tests for native mobile app via BS rests are passed but I receive
`ERROR @wdio/utils:shim: HTTPError: Response code 404 (Not Found)` when @wdio/browserstack-service tries to request BS session url - url contains `/automate`, not `/app-automate`
Issue is not reproduced if in `packages/wdio-browserstack-service/src/service.ts` update `_isAppAutomate` method with `return !!browserDesiredCapabilities['appium:app'] || !!desiredCapabilities['appium:app'] || !!desiredCapabilities['app']` locally
If I try to pass in `capabilities` custom id as `appium:app` I receive error `Error: Invalid or unsupported Webdriver capabilities found...`


### What is your expected behavior?

Error should not appear, browserstack-service should request url with `app-automate`, not with `automate`

### How to reproduce the bug.

Add to default WDIO config next attributes
```js
user: 'some_bs_user',
key: 'some_bs_key',
services: [
	['browserstack', {
		app: 'bs_custom_id',
		browserstackLocal: true,
		testObservability: false,
		opts: {
			localIdentifier: 'some_local_identifier',
		}
	}]
],
capabilities: [{
	projectName: 'some_project_name',
	buildName: 'some_build_name',
	debug: true,
	networkLogs: true,
	device: 'iPhone 14',
	os_version: '16',
}]
```
Add import:
```js
import browserstack from 'browserstack-local'
```
And add to WDIO config next hooks:
```js
onPrepare: async () => {
    console.log('Connecting local');
    return new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
        exports.bsLocal = new browserstack.Local();
        exports.bsLocal.start({
            key: exports.config.key,
            localIdentifier: 'some_local_identifier',
        }, (error: Error) => {
            if (error) return reject(error);
            console.log('Connected. Now testing...');
            resolve();
        });
    });
},

onComplete: async (exitCode, config, capabilities, results) => {
    console.log('Closing local tunnel');
    return new Promise<void>((resolve) => {
        exports.bsLocal.stop(() => {
            console.log('Stopped BrowserStackLocal');
            resolve();
        });
    });
},
```

